reviews.title: Devastated
reviews.review_text: Upon first inspection it seemed like it had durability. I braided 3 strands to create a “chain” to hold my homemade wooden whistles which weigh practically nothing. The slightest tension or tug and all three strands just pulled apart. I'm a small business owner just starting out and I will not be wasting 10$ on this product again. Lesson learned. Embarrassing in fact.
Old supply, brittle, Sliced and defective, of no use.

reviews.title: Any body feel like a fool for buying this stuff?
reviews.review_text: 1. It breaks (easily) 2. It bleeds/fades. 3. It melts when heat is applied. Long story short... Should've ordered this off of a 2 day shipping website (wink wink). Might have been a better purchase than this spool of crap I can't use!

reviews.title: -1star
reviews.review_text: Horrible. Thin. Itchy. Does not straighten out. Tried several methods. Finally returned. Still waiting on refund as I had cut a strip to use. It was unusable. Waste of time. Tired of all this crap Walmart and A are selling.

reviews.title: Terrible waste of money.
reviews.review_text: Awful. Has small cuts every here and there. This causes the cord to break if pulled making it unusable and useless. Impossible to complete project.

reviews.title: Cheap
reviews.review_text: Super flimsy stuff, save your money and go to a craft store. Snaps with the slightest pressure, tried to used for a handle wrap and turned out to be a waste of time and money

reviews.title: disappointing
reviews.review_text: Price was okay but when stringing a bead the black paint or dye flaked off.

reviews.title: uncomfortable against the skin
reviews.review_text: I bought two spools, brown and black. Looks good, but I believe it is faux suede, not leather, and have no idea what it is made of. Very uncomfortable against the skin. Too bad, as Walmart sells it in the jewelry craft section. Possibly useful for making clothes or shoe laces. Terrible for jewelry.

reviews.title: Inconsistent diameter 1.58mm to 2.94mm on spool
reviews.review_text: This cord is ok - hard and stiff but ok. The problem is that it is wildly inconsistent in the diameter. The picture I took is from 1 piece that I cut to 18". One end is 1.98mm and the other end is 2.94mm! Further into the spool it gets down to 1.58mm. I was in a bind when I bought this from Walmart. My supplier sent me the wrong size so I was scrambling to find something locally. I would not recommend buying this brand of cord if you have fixed sized ends that you are putting it into.

reviews.title: Unusable.
reviews.review_text: This is terrible. I bought it to make jewelry. Once I opened it, I only touched a piece and black dye came off on my fingers. I decided I could not make a necklace with it, because it would stain anything it was worn with. I tried to wash the dye out of a piece and see if it would be OK once dry. The amount of black dye that washed out of it just with water was unbelievable. Plus, it's very coarse and would feel uncomfortable against the skin. This is unusable.
the cord had a shiny fake look to it because of all the wax on it. cuts horrible. feels fake. you can tell a mile away.
